Further, 18 nm thin NiO films were printed (drop spacing ~50 µm) on ITO coated glass substrates held at room temperature followed by heat treating at 250, 300 and 400 °C in air for one hour and the corresponding X-ray diffraction spectra of the samples are shown in Fig. 4(b). The spectra clearly show that while the films heat treated at 250 and 300 °C are amorphous without presence of any peaks, the film heat treated at 400 °C is possibly nanocrystalline as evident from the presence of rather broad yet characteristics diffraction peaks. The average crystallite size of the NiO film annealed at 400 °C was 6.2 ± 1.8 nm confirming the nanocrystallinity, calculated from the X-ray line broadening using Scherrer formula D=0.94λβcosθ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
